1
00:00:51,500 --> 00:00:55,000
"Lost To You"

2
00:00:55,100 --> 00:00:57,700
(Episode 1)

3
00:00:59,333 --> 00:01:01,675
Some homecomings are escapes.

4
00:01:02,458 --> 00:01:05,009
Some encounters are a return to harbor.

5
00:01:12,458 --> 00:01:14,000
You got the guts to run from me?

6
00:01:14,166 --> 00:01:14,791
Where's the money?

7
00:01:15,125 --> 00:01:16,208
This month's allowance.

8
00:01:16,500 --> 00:01:17,500
It's... it's all...

9
00:01:17,666 --> 00:01:18,666
I gave it all to you.

10
00:01:18,958 --> 00:01:20,158
Please, don't come any closer.

11
00:01:22,583 --> 00:01:24,000
Ooh, so scary.

12
00:01:24,208 --> 00:01:25,583
Stay back. Stay back.

13
00:01:25,708 --> 00:01:26,708
Stay back.

14
00:01:35,250 --> 00:01:36,410
And what'll happen if you do?

15
00:01:42,583 --> 00:01:44,023
Look, another one with a death wish.

16
00:01:44,458 --> 00:01:45,708
We'll see who's dying today.

17
00:01:50,916 --> 00:01:51,916
Get him!

18
00:02:31,958 --> 00:02:32,958
Can you walk?

19
00:02:33,500 --> 00:02:34,500
Thank you.

20
00:02:36,750 --> 00:02:37,750
You're bleeding.

21
00:02:38,958 --> 00:02:39,958
I'm used to it.

22
00:02:45,666 --> 00:02:46,666
Drop dead!

23
00:02:48,458 --> 00:02:48,791
Hey.

24
00:02:48,791 --> 00:02:49,375
I didn't throw it!

25
00:02:49,541 --> 00:02:49,958
Hey.

26
00:02:50,416 --> 00:02:51,496
Are you trying to frame me?

27
00:02:52,375 --> 00:02:52,875
Are you okay?

28
00:02:53,333 --> 00:02:53,625
Let's go.

29
00:02:53,625 --> 00:02:54,625
Wake up. Hey, wake up.

30
00:02:55,208 --> 00:02:56,208
Hey.

31
00:02:56,625 --> 00:02:57,625
Hey.

32
00:03:00,208 --> 00:03:01,458
Wake up. Hey.

33
00:03:04,083 --> 00:03:04,666
Zhan Wang.

34
00:03:05,041 --> 00:03:05,625
Age 17.

35
00:03:06,041 --> 00:03:07,375
A brain tumor, right here.

36
00:03:08,375 --> 00:03:10,184
Have you been having
frequent headaches lately?

37
00:03:10,208 --> 00:03:10,791
Dizziness?

38
00:03:11,166 --> 00:03:11,833
Sudden weakness?

39
00:03:12,125 --> 00:03:14,965
Who wouldn't get a headache
listening to that old man drone on all day?

40
00:03:15,083 --> 00:03:16,643
Smoking is not allowed in the hospital.

41
00:03:18,083 --> 00:03:20,041
Your headaches are caused by the tumor.

42
00:03:20,791 --> 00:03:22,111
Although we've caught it early...

43
00:03:22,250 --> 00:03:23,375
it's highly malignant.

44
00:03:23,916 --> 00:03:25,458
If you actively undergo treatment...

45
00:03:25,916 --> 00:03:27,434
the median survival time is about...

46
00:03:27,458 --> 00:03:28,458
How long?

47
00:03:30,333 --> 00:03:31,333
Two years.

48
00:03:32,875 --> 00:03:33,915
And if I refuse treatment?

49
00:03:34,208 --> 00:03:36,088
You shouldn't be thinking
about that right now.

50
00:03:36,458 --> 00:03:37,500
If you refuse treatment...

51
00:03:37,708 --> 00:03:39,028
it will progress very quickly.

52
00:03:39,166 --> 00:03:39,750
Paralysis...

53
00:03:39,916 --> 00:03:40,916
dizziness, blindness.

54
00:03:42,166 --> 00:03:43,166
In that case...

55
00:03:43,375 --> 00:03:44,375
you won't last a year.

56
00:03:46,291 --> 00:03:47,291
One year.

57
00:03:48,375 --> 00:03:49,415
That's a pretty long time.

58
00:03:49,875 --> 00:03:50,458
Dr. Zhang.

59
00:03:50,791 --> 00:03:53,434
The patient in bed 4, his brain tumor is
worsening. He needs surgery immediately.

60
00:03:53,458 --> 00:03:54,458
Okay, I'm on my way.

61
00:03:55,083 --> 00:03:56,517
Your condition requires
immediate hospitalization.

62
00:03:56,541 --> 00:03:58,221
You need to notify your family right away.

63
00:04:12,031 --> 00:04:13,285
[Calling: "Old Thing"]

64
00:04:15,958 --> 00:04:17,666
Young Master, it's Uncle Deng.

65
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:18,958
Mr. Zhan is in a meeting.

66
00:04:18,958 --> 00:04:19,958
He can't take your call.

67
00:04:20,166 --> 00:04:21,686
If you need anything, you can tell me.

68
00:04:22,083 --> 00:04:23,083
Uncle Deng.

69
00:04:23,250 --> 00:04:24,250
Book me a ticket...

70
00:04:25,125 --> 00:04:27,045
a plane ticket back to Hong Town.

71
00:04:33,708 --> 00:04:34,708
Wang-wang.

72
00:04:34,791 --> 00:04:36,391
You have too many fights on your record.

73
00:04:36,416 --> 00:04:38,934
You'll have to go back to Hongzhen
and attend school there for a while.

74
00:04:38,958 --> 00:04:40,398
Thanks for your concern, Uncle Deng.

75
00:04:40,708 --> 00:04:41,708
My dad...

76
00:04:42,875 --> 00:04:43,915
he didn't ask anything?

77
00:04:44,833 --> 00:04:47,125
He's been busy with a
company merger recently.

78
00:04:47,208 --> 00:04:47,916
He's been too busy.

79
00:04:48,000 --> 00:04:49,000
So...

80
00:04:50,375 --> 00:04:51,208
There's one more thing.

81
00:04:51,333 --> 00:04:52,458
Your grandmother's house...

82
00:04:53,000 --> 00:04:54,360
What about my grandmother's house?

83
00:04:54,583 --> 00:04:55,943
Before the old lady passed away...

84
00:04:56,000 --> 00:04:57,600
she gave the house to another family.

85
00:04:58,375 --> 00:05:00,541
Mr. Zhan has an empty villa by the sea.

86
00:05:00,916 --> 00:05:01,541
How about...

87
00:05:01,666 --> 00:05:02,706
you stay there for now?

88
00:05:03,291 --> 00:05:04,291
Send me the address.

89
00:05:07,125 --> 00:05:08,645
According to astronomers' estimates...

90
00:05:08,791 --> 00:05:11,458
a comet is expected to draw
close to earth in three months...

91
00:05:24,583 --> 00:05:25,583
We're here, young man.

92
00:05:46,041 --> 00:05:46,500
Be good.

93
00:05:46,875 --> 00:05:47,916
Go home with your father.

94
00:05:49,333 --> 00:05:50,333
Grandma!

95
00:05:51,000 --> 00:05:52,041
I don't want to go!

96
00:05:53,000 --> 00:05:54,000
I'm not going!

97
00:05:54,500 --> 00:05:56,041
This is my home!

98
00:05:57,125 --> 00:05:58,333
Wang-wang, be strong.

99
00:05:58,958 --> 00:06:00,718
Grandma will always
be here waiting for you.

100
00:06:01,791 --> 00:06:02,791
Go.

101
00:06:03,375 --> 00:06:04,375
Let's go.

102
00:06:04,708 --> 00:06:05,708
Grandma!

103
00:06:05,750 --> 00:06:06,750
Grandma!

104
00:06:07,208 --> 00:06:08,375
Grandma!

105
00:06:12,708 --> 00:06:13,708
Grandma!

106
00:06:15,375 --> 00:06:16,375
Grandma!

107
00:06:57,208 --> 00:06:58,875
Just like the old man's style.

108
00:07:27,750 --> 00:07:29,541
"Study hard. Don't get into fights."

109
00:07:37,641 --> 00:07:39,141
(Shude Highschool)

110
00:07:48,708 --> 00:07:49,708
Wang-wang!

111
00:07:49,958 --> 00:07:51,041
Wang-wang, slow down!

112
00:07:51,458 --> 00:07:52,458
Grandma's getting old.

113
00:07:52,583 --> 00:07:53,583
I can't keep up.

114
00:07:56,375 --> 00:07:56,958
Grandma.

115
00:07:57,375 --> 00:07:58,541
Aren't you a Sea Woman?

116
00:07:58,875 --> 00:08:00,333
Even Sea Women get old.

117
00:08:00,625 --> 00:08:01,916
When Grandma gets even older...

118
00:08:02,125 --> 00:08:04,208
she'll become a wave in the great sea.

119
00:08:04,541 --> 00:08:05,083
From then on...

120
00:08:05,208 --> 00:08:06,309
when you look at the sea...

121
00:08:06,333 --> 00:08:07,875
that'll be Grandma looking at you.

122
00:08:09,416 --> 00:08:10,416
If you ever get lost...

123
00:08:10,625 --> 00:08:11,625
look.

124
00:08:11,750 --> 00:08:12,750
Look at that lighthouse.

125
00:08:12,875 --> 00:08:14,995
If you see it, you can
always find your way home.

126
00:08:16,458 --> 00:08:17,458
Grandma.

127
00:08:17,583 --> 00:08:19,041
I want to be with you forever.

128
00:08:21,041 --> 00:08:22,041
Grandma.

129
00:08:23,666 --> 00:08:24,875
Can I still find my way home?

130
00:08:49,495 --> 00:08:54,166
[A very depressing letter written to "dad"
about how this twink's life is just so sad]

131
00:09:58,375 --> 00:09:59,166
Grandma... Grandma...

132
00:09:59,333 --> 00:10:00,666
Hurry, hurry!

133
00:10:01,666 --> 00:10:02,041
Faster!

134
00:10:02,125 --> 00:10:02,666
Okay!

135
00:10:02,958 --> 00:10:03,916
Wang-wang, slow down!

136
00:10:03,916 --> 00:10:04,916
Hurry up!

137
00:10:06,583 --> 00:10:07,583
Slow down, slow down.

138
00:10:38,666 --> 00:10:40,916
Our Xiao Wang is already this tall at ten.

139
00:10:41,291 --> 00:10:42,291
Look.

140
00:10:44,000 --> 00:10:45,000
Grandma.

141
00:10:45,125 --> 00:10:48,125
One day, I'll grow
as tall as that old tree.

142
00:10:49,083 --> 00:10:50,726
I'll carry you on my back
to see faraway places.

143
00:10:50,750 --> 00:10:51,750
Okay.

144
00:10:51,916 --> 00:10:53,559
Grandma will be right here waiting for you.

145
00:10:53,583 --> 00:10:54,791
This will always be your home.

146
00:10:55,625 --> 00:10:56,625
Who are you looking for?

147
00:10:57,958 --> 00:10:59,198
What are you doing in my house?

148
00:11:02,125 --> 00:11:03,541
I should be asking you that.

149
00:11:04,416 --> 00:11:06,216
What are you doing in
my grandmother's house?

150
00:11:10,583 --> 00:11:11,583
You're...

151
00:11:12,166 --> 00:11:13,166
Zhan Wang.

152
00:11:13,458 --> 00:11:14,791
Brother, you're back.

153
00:11:15,125 --> 00:11:16,000
Just wait for me a little longer.

154
00:11:16,125 --> 00:11:17,583
I'm almost done with my homework.

155
00:11:20,375 --> 00:11:21,375
So you recognize me.

156
00:11:22,666 --> 00:11:23,833
Nervous to see me?

157
00:11:24,333 --> 00:11:25,893
Afraid I'm here to take the house back?

158
00:11:26,875 --> 00:11:27,875
How shameless.

159
00:11:28,333 --> 00:11:31,184
A whole family, perfectly able-bodied,
but you won't go out and earn a living.

160
00:11:31,208 --> 00:11:32,851
You even swindle an old
woman out of her house?

161
00:11:32,875 --> 00:11:34,075
We have never swindled anyone.

162
00:11:35,125 --> 00:11:36,405
The deed to the house is inside.

163
00:11:36,708 --> 00:11:38,601
The transfer was notarized
by the public notary office.

164
00:11:38,625 --> 00:11:39,958
When Granny Chang signed it...

165
00:11:40,041 --> 00:11:41,521
a lawyer was present as a witness.

166
00:11:42,083 --> 00:11:43,083
If you need to see it...

167
00:11:43,625 --> 00:11:44,750
I can get it for you now.

168
00:11:45,000 --> 00:11:46,000
Fine.

169
00:11:46,625 --> 00:11:47,625
You really came prepared.

170
00:11:48,833 --> 00:11:50,416
People from a small town like you...

171
00:11:51,458 --> 00:11:53,976
must be experienced at tricking
old people out of their homes, right?

172
00:11:54,000 --> 00:11:54,708
No wonder.

173
00:11:55,000 --> 00:11:56,375
A family of four, all squeezed in.

174
00:11:57,250 --> 00:11:58,810
You must have really needed this house.

175
00:12:00,125 --> 00:12:01,125
First.

176
00:12:01,708 --> 00:12:03,148
There are three people in my family.

177
00:12:03,583 --> 00:12:04,583
Second.

178
00:12:05,166 --> 00:12:06,583
We have never tricked anyone.

179
00:12:08,166 --> 00:12:09,166
And third.

180
00:12:10,958 --> 00:12:12,678
Granny Chang waited for you for five years.

181
00:12:13,750 --> 00:12:14,916
Every Lunar New Year's Eve...

182
00:12:15,666 --> 00:12:17,786
she would set an extra
place for you at the table.

183
00:12:17,875 --> 00:12:18,875
In her last six months...

184
00:12:19,333 --> 00:12:20,333
she became confused.

185
00:12:20,625 --> 00:12:22,465
She would sit by the
door every day and say...

186
00:12:23,208 --> 00:12:25,000
'Wang-wang should be coming home today.'

187
00:12:26,791 --> 00:12:27,791
And you?

188
00:12:28,250 --> 00:12:29,250
Where were you?

189
00:12:29,708 --> 00:12:30,708
I...

190
00:12:31,333 --> 00:12:32,333
You came back too late.

191
00:12:32,666 --> 00:12:34,291
This is my home now.

192
00:12:35,541 --> 00:12:36,666
Please leave.

193
00:12:39,250 --> 00:12:39,916
You make a good point.

194
00:12:40,000 --> 00:12:40,791
Don't you yell at my brother!

195
00:12:40,792 --> 00:12:42,392
You tried to take advantage of
her when she was confused...

196
00:12:42,416 --> 00:12:43,416
to...

197
00:12:51,041 --> 00:12:52,625
I didn't do it on purpose.

198
00:12:53,500 --> 00:12:55,083
He's faking it, right?

199
00:12:57,583 --> 00:12:58,250
Are you okay?

200
00:12:58,458 --> 00:12:59,458
Brother.

201
00:12:59,708 --> 00:13:02,666
Don't tell me your jinx
powers are acting up again.

202
00:13:15,916 --> 00:13:16,583
Get away from me.

203
00:13:16,708 --> 00:13:17,708
Don't touch me.

204
00:13:18,875 --> 00:13:20,125
What's your problem?

205
00:13:20,375 --> 00:13:21,958
I know my brother brought you bad luck,

206
00:13:22,375 --> 00:13:24,015
but that's no reason to be so aggressive.

207
00:13:38,916 --> 00:13:40,125
You're...

208
00:13:40,458 --> 00:13:41,833
Granny Chang's grandson.

209
00:13:43,666 --> 00:13:47,041
I think I've seen you in a photo album.

210
00:13:52,833 --> 00:13:53,833
Fine.

211
00:13:54,375 --> 00:13:55,375
Very good.

212
00:13:56,291 --> 00:13:57,291
Your family...

213
00:13:58,625 --> 00:13:59,705
This isn't over between us.

214
00:14:04,125 --> 00:14:05,125
Bro.

215
00:14:05,208 --> 00:14:06,208
You know,

216
00:14:06,833 --> 00:14:09,375
your "condition" is actually
pretty useful sometimes.

217
00:14:10,041 --> 00:14:11,125
It can scare off bad guys.

218
00:14:14,625 --> 00:14:16,583
I... I didn't mean it like that.

219
00:14:17,875 --> 00:14:18,875
I know.

220
00:14:22,208 --> 00:14:24,208
You should read less of that weird stuff.

221
00:14:30,541 --> 00:14:31,541
A jinx...?

222
00:14:35,208 --> 00:14:36,708
I don't believe that nonsense.

223
00:14:39,291 --> 00:14:40,750
I'm not that fragile.

224
00:14:41,291 --> 00:14:42,811
It's all because of this stupid tumor.

225
00:14:50,334 --> 00:14:52,125
What a phony con artist.

226
00:15:01,291 --> 00:15:02,583
A jinx, huh?

227
00:15:03,833 --> 00:15:05,473
I'm not afraid of a little more bad luck.

228
00:15:36,434 --> 00:15:38,941
(Shude High[school])

229
00:15:44,666 --> 00:15:46,833
Today, we have a new student in our class.

230
00:15:47,041 --> 00:15:48,916
He's from Jingzhou, you know.

231
00:15:49,625 --> 00:15:50,166
From Jingzhou?

232
00:15:50,167 --> 00:15:51,687
From now on, you'll all be classmates.

233
00:15:52,083 --> 00:15:53,250
So you all need to get along.

234
00:15:54,000 --> 00:15:55,291
Don't embarrass our school.

235
00:15:56,958 --> 00:15:57,416
Come on.

236
00:15:57,875 --> 00:15:58,958
Zhan Wang, come on in.

237
00:16:06,000 --> 00:16:07,000
Zhan Wang.

238
00:16:07,250 --> 00:16:08,541
Find a seat for yourself.

239
00:16:13,041 --> 00:16:14,041
Sit here! Here! Here!

240
00:16:14,291 --> 00:16:14,666
Here!

241
00:16:14,708 --> 00:16:16,208
He's so handsome.

242
00:16:22,083 --> 00:16:23,083
Over here!

243
00:16:23,125 --> 00:16:23,833
Why is he going to the back?

244
00:16:24,041 --> 00:16:25,083
Don't go any further back.

245
00:16:25,791 --> 00:16:26,250
Why?

246
00:16:26,750 --> 00:16:28,833
Because that's the Jinx.

247
00:16:34,250 --> 00:16:35,250
What are you doing?

248
00:16:40,083 --> 00:16:41,083
We meet again.

249
00:16:41,750 --> 00:16:43,190
You're better off listening to them.

250
00:16:43,625 --> 00:16:44,625
Don't sit here.

251
00:16:46,208 --> 00:16:47,208
Feeling guilty?

252
00:16:48,041 --> 00:16:49,041
Avoiding me?

253
00:16:50,875 --> 00:16:51,875
It's over.

254
00:16:52,833 --> 00:16:53,708
Do you think they knew each other before?

255
00:16:53,708 --> 00:16:54,250
Oh, right.

256
00:16:54,666 --> 00:16:55,866
I forgot to mention yesterday.

257
00:16:56,250 --> 00:16:57,250
The house.

258
00:16:57,541 --> 00:16:58,541
I'm getting it back.

259
00:16:59,583 --> 00:17:01,083
I've already had my lawyer look into

260
00:17:01,250 --> 00:17:02,809
the loopholes in the transfer documents.

261
00:17:02,833 --> 00:17:03,833
Suit yourself.

262
00:17:12,291 --> 00:17:13,291
Aren't you afraid?

263
00:17:17,541 --> 00:17:18,583
You can afford a lawyer,

264
00:17:19,125 --> 00:17:20,125
but I can't.

265
00:17:21,000 --> 00:17:22,517
Besides, my family's
paperwork is all legal.

266
00:17:22,541 --> 00:17:23,541
Investigate all you want.

267
00:17:24,458 --> 00:17:25,458
And...

268
00:17:27,583 --> 00:17:29,166
please take your hand off of me.

269
00:17:30,833 --> 00:17:31,833
Or else...

270
00:17:36,375 --> 00:17:37,375
Or else...?

271
00:17:47,083 --> 00:17:47,833
See? Bad luck.

272
00:17:47,916 --> 00:17:48,583
I told you so.

273
00:17:48,625 --> 00:17:49,458
I told you to stay away from him.

274
00:17:49,500 --> 00:17:50,684
Sitting next to him is asking for trouble.

275
00:17:50,708 --> 00:17:51,828
Quiet down, everyone. Quiet.

276
00:17:52,083 --> 00:17:53,083
Get ready for class.

277
00:18:44,041 --> 00:18:44,500
Zhan Wang.

278
00:18:45,041 --> 00:18:46,321
Zhan Wang! Zhan Wang! Zhan Wang!

279
00:18:46,541 --> 00:18:47,541
Zhan Wang.

280
00:18:48,333 --> 00:18:49,333
Zhan Wang.

281
00:18:49,791 --> 00:18:50,416
Are you okay?

282
00:18:50,750 --> 00:18:51,958
Are you hurt anywhere?

283
00:18:58,416 --> 00:18:59,416
What's wrong?

284
00:19:00,208 --> 00:19:01,208
I'm perfectly fine.

285
00:19:01,250 --> 00:19:01,875
Incredible.

286
00:19:02,166 --> 00:19:03,351
You sat with the Jinx all morning,

287
00:19:03,375 --> 00:19:04,375
and you're still alive.

288
00:19:04,583 --> 00:19:05,583
The Jinx?

289
00:19:06,500 --> 00:19:07,740
You guys are talking about him?

290
00:19:08,416 --> 00:19:09,458
Why is he a jinx?

291
00:19:09,625 --> 00:19:10,625
Tell me about it.

292
00:19:11,125 --> 00:19:12,125
Xu Yuan...

293
00:19:12,208 --> 00:19:13,488
He doesn't just jinx his family.

294
00:19:13,708 --> 00:19:15,166
Even his friends around him...

295
00:19:15,291 --> 00:19:16,291
suffer terrible luck.

296
00:19:16,333 --> 00:19:17,333
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

297
00:19:17,708 --> 00:19:18,708
It's not just bad luck.

298
00:19:18,958 --> 00:19:19,958
It's life-threatening.

299
00:19:20,750 --> 00:19:22,630
Old Wu from next door
went out to sea with him,

300
00:19:22,916 --> 00:19:24,059
and almost didn't make it back.

301
00:19:24,083 --> 00:19:25,083
I heard about that.

302
00:19:25,750 --> 00:19:27,208
Xu Yuan was only twelve back then.

303
00:19:27,416 --> 00:19:28,559
He went out to sea with a neighbor.

304
00:19:28,583 --> 00:19:29,916
The engine failed for no reason.

305
00:19:30,166 --> 00:19:31,583
Everyone on the boat nearly died.

306
00:19:32,583 --> 00:19:34,041
You guys are exaggerating.

307
00:19:34,500 --> 00:19:35,726
How can you blame something like that...

308
00:19:35,750 --> 00:19:37,541
on a twelve-year-old kid?

309
00:19:38,000 --> 00:19:39,280
It's not an exaggeration at all.

310
00:19:39,541 --> 00:19:40,581
I saw it with my own eyes.

311
00:19:41,000 --> 00:19:42,934
Xu Yuan and I were in the
same class in middle school.

312
00:19:42,958 --> 00:19:44,078
One night during study hall,

313
00:19:44,208 --> 00:19:45,642
he tapped the shoulder of
the person in front of him.

314
00:19:45,666 --> 00:19:46,333
And guess what happened?

315
00:19:46,625 --> 00:19:47,625
What?

316
00:19:48,250 --> 00:19:49,708
The ceiling fan fell right down.

317
00:19:50,291 --> 00:19:52,211
It landed exactly where
that person was sitting.

318
00:19:52,625 --> 00:19:53,416
Also, also...

319
00:19:53,541 --> 00:19:55,141
The same thing happened to his deskmate.

320
00:19:55,333 --> 00:19:56,333
I also know about...

321
00:19:56,416 --> 00:19:57,708
the incident on the bus.

322
00:19:58,208 --> 00:19:59,208
What incident?

323
00:19:59,500 --> 00:20:02,083
That night, the bus was running normally.

324
00:20:02,583 --> 00:20:03,291
Then suddenly,

325
00:20:03,500 --> 00:20:04,500
out of nowhere,

326
00:20:04,666 --> 00:20:05,875
the bus just stopped.

327
00:20:06,208 --> 00:20:07,208
All the passengers...

328
00:20:07,416 --> 00:20:08,601
were thrown from their seats.

329
00:20:08,625 --> 00:20:09,416
That's terrifying.

330
00:20:09,625 --> 00:20:11,185
And you know what the craziest part is?

331
00:20:11,625 --> 00:20:13,465
Xu Yuan was sitting
right next to the driver.

332
00:20:15,458 --> 00:20:16,458
So this Xu Yuan...

333
00:20:16,583 --> 00:20:17,583
isn't just a jinx.

334
00:20:18,500 --> 00:20:19,541
He's like the Grim Reaper.

335
00:20:20,333 --> 00:20:20,791
Pretty much.

336
00:20:20,916 --> 00:20:21,541
Yeah, yeah, the Grim Reaper.

337
00:20:21,541 --> 00:20:22,291
So, you see,

338
00:20:22,458 --> 00:20:23,601
not a single student in our class...

339
00:20:23,625 --> 00:20:24,625
dares to sit near him.

340
00:20:24,666 --> 00:20:25,375
For three years,

341
00:20:25,500 --> 00:20:26,500
you're the first one.

342
00:20:26,583 --> 00:20:27,583
So...

343
00:20:27,833 --> 00:20:29,273
he doesn't even have any friends?

344
00:20:30,041 --> 00:20:31,041
He did.

345
00:20:31,916 --> 00:20:32,291
Who?

346
00:20:32,416 --> 00:20:33,616
That upperclassman, Xiang Bei.

347
00:20:33,875 --> 00:20:34,915
The one who broke his leg?

348
00:20:35,625 --> 00:20:37,017
- I don't know him.
- Right, right.

349
00:20:37,041 --> 00:20:38,521
Xiang Bei, he's that student athlete.

350
00:20:38,833 --> 00:20:39,416
Let me tell you,

351
00:20:39,666 --> 00:20:41,306
he used to be really close with Xu Yuan.

352
00:20:41,333 --> 00:20:43,093
He wouldn't listen to
anyone who warned him.

353
00:20:43,166 --> 00:20:44,606
- And then?
- And as it turned out...

354
00:20:50,666 --> 00:20:51,826
Everything they said is true.

355
00:20:52,583 --> 00:20:53,583
You should change seats.

356
00:20:55,625 --> 00:20:56,625
I'm not afraid.

357
00:20:58,750 --> 00:20:59,750
After all,

358
00:21:00,875 --> 00:21:02,595
who could possibly have worse luck than me?

359
00:21:03,166 --> 00:21:04,375
If you refuse treatment,

360
00:21:04,625 --> 00:21:06,101
your condition will deteriorate rapidly.

361
00:21:06,125 --> 00:21:07,125
Blindness, paralysis...

362
00:21:07,625 --> 00:21:08,625
At this rate,

363
00:21:08,916 --> 00:21:09,916
you won't last a year.

364
00:21:15,291 --> 00:21:16,291
Today,

365
00:21:17,083 --> 00:21:18,833
I, Zhan Wang, want to see for myself...

366
00:21:20,166 --> 00:21:21,366
by being Xu Yuan's friend,

367
00:21:22,833 --> 00:21:24,313
just how unlucky a person can become.

368
00:21:58,458 --> 00:21:58,916
Having fun?

369
00:21:59,208 --> 00:22:00,208
Heaps.

370
00:22:01,000 --> 00:22:02,000
What do you want from me?

371
00:22:02,291 --> 00:22:03,291
I just want to see

372
00:22:03,875 --> 00:22:07,208
what the Jinx who scammed my
grandma out of her house is really like.

373
00:22:08,375 --> 00:22:09,375
Do what you want.

374
00:22:45,125 --> 00:22:46,125
Jinx.

375
00:23:18,333 --> 00:23:19,373
Hurry, let's go. Let's go.

376
00:23:22,000 --> 00:23:23,000
Here, here, here.

377
00:23:53,041 --> 00:23:54,208
We ran into him again.

378
00:23:59,541 --> 00:24:00,941
Do they always treat you like this?

379
00:24:01,166 --> 00:24:02,166
I'm a jinx.

380
00:24:02,583 --> 00:24:03,208
This is normal.

381
00:24:03,500 --> 00:24:04,540
Doesn't it make you angry?

382
00:24:05,041 --> 00:24:06,401
What's the point of getting angry?

383
00:24:07,000 --> 00:24:08,680
So you don't want to do anything about it?

384
00:24:08,916 --> 00:24:09,916
Like what?

385
00:24:10,708 --> 00:24:11,541
Go door to door explaining

386
00:24:11,625 --> 00:24:12,625
that I'm not a jinx?

387
00:24:13,041 --> 00:24:15,241
Or get on my knees and beg
them not to be afraid of me?

388
00:24:16,958 --> 00:24:18,038
I can beat them up for you.

389
00:24:19,583 --> 00:24:20,583
And then what?

390
00:24:21,083 --> 00:24:22,403
Make them even more scared of me?

391
00:24:23,041 --> 00:24:24,458
Have the whole town say,

392
00:24:24,833 --> 00:24:25,833
"Look,

393
00:24:25,875 --> 00:24:27,458
the Jinx brought a thug with him"?

394
00:24:28,083 --> 00:24:29,083
Stay out of my business.

395
00:24:30,458 --> 00:24:31,708
Worry about your own family.

396
00:24:32,916 --> 00:24:35,036
You left your sick grandmother
here for so many years

397
00:24:35,875 --> 00:24:37,291
and never even came back to visit.

398
00:24:38,708 --> 00:24:40,468
I try to help, and this
is the thanks I get?

399
00:24:40,958 --> 00:24:43,718
And you have the nerve to lecture
me while you're living in my house?

400
00:24:45,318 --> 00:24:46,545
["Tear down"]

401
00:24:49,583 --> 00:24:50,583
A-Mei.

402
00:24:50,625 --> 00:24:52,865
Your noodle-making skills
are getting better and better.

403
00:24:54,208 --> 00:24:55,875
Who are you making this special for?

404
00:24:56,666 --> 00:24:57,708
You old rascal.

405
00:24:57,987 --> 00:24:59,517
I learned from your wife several times.

406
00:24:59,541 --> 00:24:59,750
Really?

407
00:24:59,750 --> 00:25:00,750
You couldn't tell?

408
00:25:01,916 --> 00:25:02,875
Seriously.

409
00:25:02,876 --> 00:25:03,996
You're always joking around.

410
00:25:04,666 --> 00:25:05,666
Xiao Yuan is back.

411
00:25:07,166 --> 00:25:07,583
Mom.

412
00:25:07,666 --> 00:25:08,906
Did you write the sign outside?

413
00:25:09,041 --> 00:25:10,041
It's not bad.

414
00:25:11,333 --> 00:25:13,500
Xiao... Xiao Yuan brought
a friend to the shop.

415
00:25:13,791 --> 00:25:14,416
Come, come.

416
00:25:14,708 --> 00:25:15,708
Come sit, come sit.

417
00:25:15,833 --> 00:25:16,166
What would you like to eat?

418
00:25:16,166 --> 00:25:16,500
Mom.

419
00:25:16,500 --> 00:25:17,041
My treat.

420
00:25:17,041 --> 00:25:17,541
He's not...

421
00:25:17,583 --> 00:25:17,958
Come on.

422
00:25:18,125 --> 00:25:19,125
Have a seat, have a seat.

423
00:25:19,250 --> 00:25:20,250
Sit here, sit here.

424
00:25:20,708 --> 00:25:21,708
Sit down.

425
00:25:22,041 --> 00:25:22,625
What would you like to eat?

426
00:25:22,750 --> 00:25:24,166
Our broth is really fresh.

427
00:25:24,500 --> 00:25:25,601
Fish balls, seafood noodles.

428
00:25:25,625 --> 00:25:26,291
What would you like?

429
00:25:26,583 --> 00:25:28,103
I'll go make you some seafood noodles.

430
00:25:28,166 --> 00:25:29,166
With extra seafood.

431
00:25:29,458 --> 00:25:30,665
It's the first time Xiao Yuan
has brought a friend over.

432
00:25:30,666 --> 00:25:31,666
Mom.

433
00:25:32,875 --> 00:25:34,041
He's Granny Chang's grandson.

434
00:25:34,458 --> 00:25:35,458
Zhan Wang.

435
00:25:46,750 --> 00:25:47,750
Wang-wang, right?

436
00:25:49,291 --> 00:25:50,958
I'll go make you some fish balls.

437
00:25:51,750 --> 00:25:52,750
No, thanks.

438
00:25:54,541 --> 00:25:55,541
Let's go, let's go.

439
00:26:11,916 --> 00:26:12,916
Thanks.

440
00:26:18,041 --> 00:26:20,161
Your family is okay with
them treating you like this?

441
00:26:20,666 --> 00:26:21,666
They're used to it.

442
00:26:36,541 --> 00:26:38,125
Time to eat. Stop playing.

443
00:26:38,625 --> 00:26:39,083
Wang-wang.

444
00:26:39,416 --> 00:26:40,416
Come, look.

445
00:26:40,500 --> 00:26:42,875
Grandma bought you
your favorite fish balls.

446
00:26:43,666 --> 00:26:44,666
Come and try some.

447
00:26:44,916 --> 00:26:46,125
Wang-wang, try it.

448
00:27:04,750 --> 00:27:05,750
Is it good?

449
00:27:05,916 --> 00:27:06,916
It's good.

450
00:27:26,291 --> 00:27:27,291
Finish up and go home.

451
00:27:27,666 --> 00:27:28,746
My mom's about to close up.

452
00:27:37,250 --> 00:27:39,583
That Wang-wang is pretty tall.

453
00:27:39,916 --> 00:27:41,666
He's just like how Granny Chang said.

454
00:27:42,500 --> 00:27:43,833
You two are about the same age.

455
00:27:44,416 --> 00:27:45,833
If you two could be friends...

456
00:27:46,139 --> 00:27:47,139
wouldn't that be nice?

457
00:27:47,569 --> 00:27:49,089
Leaving his grandma all alone in town,

458
00:27:49,250 --> 00:27:50,610
not even caring when she was sick.

459
00:27:50,916 --> 00:27:52,196
How can you call him a good kid?

460
00:27:52,541 --> 00:27:54,041
But Granny Chang said...

461
00:27:54,375 --> 00:27:55,535
his family had their reasons.

462
00:27:55,666 --> 00:27:58,066
Having reasons is no excuse to
abandon your own grandmother.

463
00:28:02,708 --> 00:28:04,684
He didn't even see her one
last time before she passed.

464
00:28:04,708 --> 00:28:06,748
And the second he's back,
he's demanding the house.

465
00:28:06,875 --> 00:28:07,916
Xiao Yuan.

466
00:28:08,083 --> 00:28:09,083
Mom.

467
00:28:09,625 --> 00:28:10,625
I'm heading home now.

468
00:28:10,666 --> 00:28:12,106
I have to work at the docks tonight.

469
00:28:14,000 --> 00:28:15,500
Be careful at work.

470
00:28:17,458 --> 00:28:18,458
That boy...

471
00:28:27,625 --> 00:28:28,041
Bro.

472
00:28:28,583 --> 00:28:29,783
Who are you daydreaming about?

473
00:28:30,291 --> 00:28:32,500
That grumpy Zhan Wang?

474
00:28:33,333 --> 00:28:34,813
Go to your room and do your homework.

475
00:28:35,458 --> 00:28:37,208
Mom told me everything.

476
00:28:37,458 --> 00:28:38,833
He's Granny Chang's grandson.

477
00:28:39,333 --> 00:28:40,333
He used to live here.

478
00:28:40,625 --> 00:28:42,666
Now you're living in his old room,

479
00:28:43,250 --> 00:28:44,916
sleeping in his old bed.

480
00:28:45,416 --> 00:28:46,915
So, does that make you two...

481
00:28:46,916 --> 00:28:47,916
No.

482
00:28:49,791 --> 00:28:50,833
He even announced today...

483
00:28:50,916 --> 00:28:52,291
that he wants to be your friend.

484
00:28:52,791 --> 00:28:54,333
Although his method...

485
00:28:55,208 --> 00:28:56,833
was a bit strange.

486
00:29:01,000 --> 00:29:02,000
How do you know that?

487
00:29:02,125 --> 00:29:03,916
It's all over school.

488
00:29:04,291 --> 00:29:06,833
What can I say? You're
a legend in Hong Town.

489
00:29:08,208 --> 00:29:13,520
I just wanted to see what kind of person the
jinx who scammed my grandma out of her house is.

490
00:29:16,375 --> 00:29:18,041
He's just trying to give me a hard time.

491
00:29:20,916 --> 00:29:22,166
I don't think so.

492
00:29:22,625 --> 00:29:25,000
If this were a novel,

493
00:29:25,416 --> 00:29:27,750
you two would be fated rivals.

494
00:29:27,916 --> 00:29:28,916
Or soulmates.

495
00:29:29,375 --> 00:29:30,855
You should read less of that garbage.

496
00:29:31,583 --> 00:29:32,291
Bro.

497
00:29:32,416 --> 00:29:33,541
Life is short.

498
00:29:33,750 --> 00:29:34,767
When you meet someone special,

499
00:29:34,791 --> 00:29:36,000
you have to seize the moment.

500
00:29:36,375 --> 00:29:38,455
Do you still want me to
pay for your acting classes?

501
00:29:39,500 --> 00:29:40,541
Yes!

502
00:29:40,833 --> 00:29:41,833
Bro.

503
00:29:43,750 --> 00:29:44,750
Then shut it.

504
00:29:45,958 --> 00:29:46,958
Yes, sir.

505
00:30:04,583 --> 00:30:05,583
Uncle Wang.

506
00:30:08,208 --> 00:30:09,291
You're here again?

507
00:30:09,458 --> 00:30:10,458
I already told you.

508
00:30:10,500 --> 00:30:11,500
This work is dangerous.

509
00:30:11,750 --> 00:30:12,750
We don't hire students.

510
00:30:13,125 --> 00:30:14,125
Uncle Wang.

511
00:30:14,416 --> 00:30:16,458
I really need the money.

512
00:30:17,583 --> 00:30:19,343
My sister's training
class is starting soon,

513
00:30:19,916 --> 00:30:21,316
and I'm still short three thousand.

514
00:30:21,875 --> 00:30:23,083
But with your build...

515
00:30:28,708 --> 00:30:29,708
All right.

516
00:30:30,208 --> 00:30:31,791
There's a shipment to unload tonight.

517
00:30:32,166 --> 00:30:33,166
Midnight to 4 a.m.

518
00:30:33,541 --> 00:30:34,666
Pay is two hundred. You in?

519
00:30:34,791 --> 00:30:35,166
I'm in.

520
00:30:35,583 --> 00:30:36,791
But let me be clear.

521
00:30:37,083 --> 00:30:37,541
The cargo...

522
00:30:37,916 --> 00:30:39,196
If you break it, you pay for it.

523
00:30:39,333 --> 00:30:40,773
If you get hurt, you're on your own.

524
00:30:41,125 --> 00:30:42,208
Letting you do this job...

525
00:30:42,625 --> 00:30:44,083
is already a huge risk for me.

526
00:30:44,750 --> 00:30:45,750
I understand.

527
00:30:46,250 --> 00:30:47,583
Fine. Go get changed.

528
00:30:48,000 --> 00:30:49,000
Thanks, Uncle.

529
00:31:02,250 --> 00:31:02,750
Look.

530
00:31:03,166 --> 00:31:03,875
That kid's here again.

531
00:31:04,125 --> 00:31:04,916
He's had a tough life, too.

532
00:31:05,041 --> 00:31:06,166
Isn't his dad the one who...

533
00:31:06,833 --> 00:31:08,353
Get to work, get to work, get to work.

534
00:31:15,458 --> 00:31:17,416
How can he be that desperate for money?

535
00:32:15,041 --> 00:32:15,583
Xiao Wang.

536
00:32:16,000 --> 00:32:17,000
I found it.

537
00:32:17,500 --> 00:32:19,380
The Xu family is in
serious financial trouble.

538
00:32:19,833 --> 00:32:22,033
The noodle shop makes less
than three thousand a month.

539
00:32:22,500 --> 00:32:24,083
Xu Yuan's father is deceased.

540
00:32:24,291 --> 00:32:25,611
His mother has a chronic illness.

541
00:32:26,291 --> 00:32:27,531
The medical bills must be high.

542
00:32:33,708 --> 00:32:34,708
Keep digging.

543
00:33:10,125 --> 00:33:11,125
Grandma.

544
00:33:12,208 --> 00:33:13,208
If you knew...

545
00:33:13,625 --> 00:33:15,625
they were tricking you for money,

546
00:33:17,125 --> 00:33:18,805
would you still have given them the house?

547
00:33:20,625 --> 00:33:22,041
Why did it go to him?

548
00:33:24,000 --> 00:33:25,625
Wasn't that house supposed to be mine?

549
00:33:27,700 --> 00:33:31,220
(Wang-wang: No matter how far you go, Grandma
will be here waiting for you to come home.)
